  "body": "Seems Hetzner doesn't like current solution (does alert as \"port scanning\" activity):  \r\n```\r\nl, err := net.Listen(\"tcp6\", fmt.Sprintf(\":%d\", port))\r\n\tif err != nil {\r\n\t\tisDisabled := strings.Contains(err.Error(), \"cannot assign requested address\") || strings.Contains(err.Error(), \"address family not supported by protocol\")\r\n\t\tif !isDisabled {\r\n\t\t\tlog.Warn(\"can't enable ipv6\", \"err\", err)\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t} \r\n```\r\n\r\nBut I don't know cross-platform lib for Go.\r\n\r\nAs a hot-fix we can:\r\n- On linux move to `/sys/module/ipv6/parameters/disable` see https://www.golinuxcloud.com/linux-check-ipv6-enabled/\r\n- On other systems just disable `ipv6` until user's complain\r\n\r\n\r\nOptionaly can:\r\n- try to find some cross-platform lib for this, maybe on C/Java \r\n- do something for Win (but I don't know how much dependencies has this solution - does it depend on exact terminal syntax?): https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2083412/detect-if-ipv6-is-enabled-on-windows-machines\r\n\r\n\r\nRelated to https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/issues/6034#issuecomment-1325596391 , https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/issues/6067 , https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/pull/6093",
